      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "To elucidate the in vivo function of OsDr1 and OsDrAp1, we used the tobacco protoplast transfection assay. p35S4Gal4::GUS ( Figure 5A ) was used as the reporter, in which a chimeric promoter consisting of the 35S enhancer/tetramer of the GAL4 binding site/bean ␤ -phaseolin storage protein gene minimal promoter ( Ϫ 65 to ϩ 80) was fused with the GUS open reading frame. p35S::LUC, which contained a 35S promoter/luciferase gene fusion, was used as an internal control for the transfection experiments."
